# Isaac Sim Installation Guide
### Baker Hughes R&T — ACB Project

---

## Prerequisites

- Windows 10/11 with PowerShell
- NVIDIA GPU (RTX recommended)
- Admin access not required
- **Firewall access must be requested before installation** (see below)

---

## Step 1: Request Firewall Access

Before cloning or building anything, submit a firewall ticket to unblock 
the NVIDIA packman bootstrap server.

1. Go to: `[link to BH firewall request portal]`
2. Fill in the form:
   - **Source:** your machine IP
   - **Destination:** `99.84.215.47, 99.84.215.92, 99.84.215.16, 99.84.215.102`
   - **Service:** `https`
   - **Business Justification:** Isaac Sim build pipeline requires outbound 
     HTTPS access to `bootstrap.packman.nvidia.com` (AWS CloudFront CDN) 
     to download build dependencies for the ACB simulation project.
3. Wait for approval before proceeding.

> ⚠️ **Note:** These IPs belong to AWS CloudFront and may change over time. 
> If the build fails with SSL errors in the future, run `nslookup bootstrap.packman.nvidia.com` 
> and submit a new ticket with the updated IPs.

